    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A top-down, dashboard-style SPA. It starts with a high-level summary, then flows into four distinct, interactive modules: 1) Market Anatomy, 2) Competitive Arena, 3) Consumer Insights, and 4) Strategic Blueprint. This structure allows users to get a quick overview from the charts and key stats, then dive deeper into the specific areas that interest them most. Navigation is handled by both scrolling and header links for quick access. This non-linear, thematic approach is more user-friendly for data exploration than the linear format of the original report. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Market Segmentation: Report Info -> 4 key belt types. Goal -> Show market composition. Viz -> Interactive Doughnut Chart (Chart.js). Interaction -> Clicking a segment updates a detailed text block. Justification -> Visually intuitive way to show parts of a whole and allow for drill-down.
        - Competitive Landscape: Report Info -> Competitors by tier/price. Goal -> Compare players. Viz -> Interactive Polar Area Chart (Chart.js) to show different strategic groups. Interaction -> Clicking a brand on the chart or list reveals a detailed card with strategies/weaknesses. Justification -> A polar chart effectively groups competitors into their strategic archetypes (Value, Incumbent, etc.), making the landscape easy to grasp.
        - Market Currents: Report Info -> Belt hole obsolescence & stretch mandate. Goal -> Show technological shifts. Viz -> HTML/CSS side-by-side comparison cards with icons. Interaction -> None needed, direct comparison is the goal. Justification -> Clear, static visual comparison is most effective for this binary concept.
        - Strategic Blueprint: Report Info -> Product/GTM recommendations. Goal -> Inform action plan. Viz -> Structured HTML/CSS layout with icons. Interaction -> None. Justification -> A clear, readable, and well-organized text layout is best for presenting a strategic plan.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
